{"source_key":"sha256-d0cd95f7d5f39f4b80f68f088e38f04c","record_index":27,"record_hash":"sha256:c1b6f55c0bee6465f5581a363ee591c13d45c4b6619bfb5a53ace3aee6890d7e","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:08:24.560Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 153f7c\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1137\nOutput:\n# GitButler Cloud\n\nA private GitButler sync, backup, and takeover service built on top of\n[code.storage](https://code.storage).\n\nUsers sign up in the browser, approve a CLI device login, and then use\n`but-login`, `but-sync`, and `but-takeover` to move private GitButler refs\nbetween machines. The server proxies Git Smart HTTP to backing code.storage\nrepositories using short-lived JWTs signed by your org private key.\n\nSee [`PLAN.md`](./PLAN.md) for the architecture writeup.\n\n## Stack\n\n- Next.js 15 (App Router, Node runtime) + TypeScript\n- Drizzle ORM + PlanetScale MySQL in every environment.\n- `iron-session` cookie auth, `bcryptjs` password hashes\n- `jose` for ES256 JWT signing\n- Rust CLI workspace for `but-login`, `but-sync`, `but-cloud`, and `but-takeover`\n- Tailwind CSS\n\n## Setup\n\n1. Copy and edit env:\n   ```bash\n   cp .env.example .env\n   # then set DATABASE_HOST, DATABASE_USERNAME, DATABASE_PASSWORD,\n   # PIERRE_ORG_NAME, PIERRE_PRIVATE_KEY, and SESSION_SECRET\n   ```\n2. Install + initialize the DB:\n   ```bash\n   pnpm install\n   pnpm db:push\n   ```\n3. Run it:\n   ```bash\n   pnpm dev\n   ```\n\n## Try it end-to-end\n\n```bash\n# 1. Start the local server and sign up at http://localhost:3000/signup\npnpm dev\n\n# 2. In a Git repo, start CLI auth against local development and approve the printed URL\ncargo run -p but-cloud-cli --bin but-login -- --server http://localhost:3000\n\n# 3. Force-sync local branches and refs/meta/* to the cloud.\n#    The checkout gets its own gitbutler.cloudClientId in .git/config.\n#    Temporary wip commits are created during sync by default; pass --no-wip to disable.\ncargo run -p but-cloud-cli --bin but-sync\n\n# 4. Take over a branch from another synced client\ncargo run -p but-cloud-cli --bin but-takeover -- <client_id>/<branch>\n#    This stashes dirty work, unapplies other active GitButler branches,\n#    and picks cloud-only commits into the local target branch.\n\n# 5. Inspect synced cloud\n[TRUNCATED]\nconfig --local gitbutler.cloudUser schacon2\n```\n\n## Layout\n\n```\napp/\n  signup/, login/, cli/device/[code]/\n  settings/cloud/                   # CLI client revocation\n  api/auth/{signup,login,logout}/   # cookie-auth JSON APIs\n  api/cli/device/*                  # device auth flow\n  api/cloud/projects/resolve        # cloud project provisioning\n  api/cloud/git/[project]/*         # streaming Git Smart HTTP proxy\ncrates/but-cloud-cli/\n  src/bin/{but-cloud,but-login,but-sync,but-takeover}.rs\nlib/\n  db.ts            # Drizzle-backed query facade\n  databaseUrl.ts   # builds PlanetScale DATABASE_URL from env pieces\n  session.ts       # iron-session helpers\n  cloudAuth.ts     # CLI token/device helpers\n  cloudProject.ts  # project identity helpers\n  codeStorage.ts   # mintJwt(), createCodeStorageRepo()\n  cloudGitProxy.ts # cloud Git proxy\n  validation.ts    # username / repo / email validators\nmiddleware.ts      # rewrites cloud and compatibility Git Smart HTTP paths\ndb/schema.ts\ndrizzle.config.ts\n```\n\n## Notes / gotchas\n\n- All proxy routes pin `runtime = 'nodejs'` and `dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`\n  because they stream request bodies via `fetch(..., { duplex: 'half' })`.\n- Only the `Content-Type`, `Accept`, `Accept-Encoding`, `User-Agent`, and\n  `Git-Protocol` request headers are forwarded upstream; everything else\n  (including `Authorization`) is replaced with our minted JWT.\n- Each push/clone request mints a fresh 5‑minute JWT scoped to the single\n  backing repo. `git:read` for upload‑pack, `git:read`+`git:write` for\n  receive‑pack.\n- Cloud tokens are SHA-256 hashed at rest; the plaintext is returned once to\n  the polling CLI.\n- Reserved usernames (`api`, `dashboard`, `login`, `new`, `settings`,\n  `signup`, `cloud`, `_next`, …) are blocked at signup so they can't shadow app\n  routes.\n\n## Out of scope for v0\n\nWeb code browser, issues/PRs, collaborators, orgs/teams, OAuth providers,\nwebhooks, billing, rate limiting, audit logs, SSH transport. See `PLAN.md`\nsection 12 for where each of these would slot in.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:08:24.560Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}